 Nigerian singer Rema has announced that he would be dropping his album this year 2021. Rema took to his twitter page to make this announcement. According to the ‘Dumebi’ singer, his album would be released this year on Monday, January 4, 2020. Album, yes. — REMA (@heisrema) January 4, 2021 Album title and release date are still unknown. So far, Rema released three bodies of work within his first eight months as a signed artist. The projects are Rema Freestyle EP, Rema EP and Bad Commando.